  "title": "sEEG Forced Two-Choice Task",
  "description": "This dataset comprises stereoelectroencephalography (sEEG) recordings from patients performing a forced two-choice response task, collected in the epilepsy monitoring unit at Oregon Health & Science University. The data extends characterization of movement-related neural oscillations by providing intracranial recordings from deep brain structures. This resource enables investigation of canonical motor-related activity patterns across distributed neural networks.",
  "methods_description": "Stereoelectroencephalography data were collected from patients performing a forced two-choice response task in the epilepsy monitoring unit at Oregon Health & Science University, in collaboration with the University of Oregon.",
